      "author_association": "MEMBER",
      "body": "You should not be creating a bitcoin-qt.conf file, or try to modify any settings within it. This file is created and handled by the Qt library and is not meant to be user modified. It's where the setting set in the GUI are saved. Instead you should be using a bitcoin.conf file in your datadir. Command line arguments and bitcoin.conf options will override any of the settings set from within the GUI (aka all the things in bitcoin-qt.conf).\r\n\r\nbitcoin-qt checks for the existence of the datadir. So just make sure the datadir exists and the welcome dialog won't appear.",
